<subSubSection id="E456156E2A1632B694C3928768E847A6" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="D799C090DF124D6C87340EE9F23C64FF" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
<taxonomicName id="5221BA2C42573BC5A3E97CA0A221F3F8" authority="(L.) P. B." class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Setaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="italica">
Setaria 
<normalizedToken id="DB9876C2F519760D9BACA7EECEDE72EA" originalValue="itálica" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">italica</normalizedToken>
(
<authorityName id="4DE044DA3F0AC81C7FADB7C1AE153989" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">L.</authorityName>
) P. B.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="458CBEA7A94B9BC011D775CC9E3B2727" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="4C9AD125CEF21327DA2025B6C898215C" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Kolbenhirse, Vogelhirse</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="B2A09D86C357080CBC8E5C7405A5D0C6" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" type="description">
<paragraph id="80D674197BB12882BB12A6F58EF03217" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
Unterscheidet sich von allen vorhergehenden Arten durch folgende Merkmale: Bis 1,2 m hoch; 
<emphasis id="9BAA2A0A1EB0D6A32564B5BD92D281A0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
Durchmesser des 
<normalizedToken id="EEB615A1FA17248CB89231202F95C001" originalValue="Blütenstandes" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Bluetenstandes</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
(ohne sterile 
<normalizedToken id="73640ED5238B425516E0501DB4EC8ED0" originalValue="Rispenäste" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Rispenaeste</normalizedToken>
!) 
<emphasis id="FD82EC6C770EF7FD9027CA2F4BC76C38" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
1,5-2,5 cm; Hauptachse des 
<normalizedToken id="FC9317F3BAEF518069EAC27B4DEE64F5" originalValue="Blütenstandes" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Bluetenstandes</normalizedToken>
dicht mit 0,5-1 mm langen Haaren besetzt; 
<normalizedToken id="CBAEFD3A2E117779B5B0D935A7F42C35" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
nicht als Ganzes abfallend, die 
<normalizedToken id="BD244C39AADDCB124B6FA62F99562931" originalValue="Hüllspelzen" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Huellspelzen</normalizedToken>
bleiben stehen
</emphasis>
. - 
<normalizedToken id="CA513E80D640C02DAD097DD407F67291" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer und Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B33F538487879CFD6F378821652CDFF1" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="65114184B3013A724355DF49D427520D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 18:</emphasis>
Material aus 
<taxonomicName id="B14D2AD8A6A31D41E4EFA20FDA5E1277" authority="(Kishimoto 1938)" baseAuthorityName="Kishimoto" baseAuthorityYear="1938" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Baldingera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosa">Formosa (Kishimoto 1938)</taxonomicName>
; aus Indien, Meiosen normal (Chandola 1959), Singh und Godward 1961, aus Florida und Uruguay (Bowden und Senn 1962). Weitere 
<normalizedToken id="BB8281CA553AC36AFD05A4246440B3DC" originalValue="übereinstimmende" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">uebereinstimmende</normalizedToken>
Angaben in 
<normalizedToken id="05ED676BC1C7CE6D8466ACF0516D2C2A" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="B0F9BBF15A1CC6AE4D9103A50D18FA38" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Loeve</normalizedToken>
(1961).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="54E5899134E190AA26035D86F07108A8" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="D7D2ECEEB48250F76DE221B74E2AA834" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Standort.</emphasis>
Wie 
<taxonomicName id="C605208505C168461C675C0A0F716B9B" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Setaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis id="FD2EDAAF4DE564CCE675A693BBFDE7D5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">S. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1). Im Gebiet selten mehr angebaut (Vogelfutter), gelegentlich verwildert.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EEF6C02421BA42CBA449C802A00B5B54" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="5A21471F0BE61A36222CC3068454076D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Verbreitung. Pflanze mit weltweiter Verbreitung:</emphasis>
Tropen und Subtropen der ganzen Erde; teilweise heute noch wichtige Kulturpflanze, die aus 
<taxonomicName id="1D0A097E7E4C638F3F8799381574972D" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Setaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="AF532E8E8767527D9EDA1259A938473F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">S. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 4) entstanden sein soll. - Im Gebiet nur in den 
<normalizedToken id="E3F5475309F160D030636ED789CCA2A6" originalValue="wärmsten" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">waermsten</normalizedToken>
Gegenden; selten (eingeschleppt oder Kulturrelikt).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D01DB280023B08D9907C0AE64FD49061" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis id="16805F7399F5DA5289FE9DAB1DC51E50" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="620F91DE686C893D0C2DEE3FC029EDE5" originalValue="Übergangsformen" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">Uebergangsformen</normalizedToken>
zwischen 
<taxonomicName id="8E2F19FF426252808B008E83CF996776" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Setaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="D5F04F886A1116130FC66A0FF28FE145" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">S. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="66D7FF94C503D3113776BDBD4661B78A" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Setaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="italica">
<emphasis id="DF356854FABCC604FB395A8DC810EB16" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">S. italica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sollten untersucht werden; nach der bei Platzer (1962) zitierten Literatur ist 
<taxonomicName id="93304F510479463266E7ECEE4EB03C5B" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Setaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="EEE63964C374A2CA509D5F9E4A94E0F9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">S. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
die Stammart von 
<taxonomicName id="EF54CDC9A867AD35BB9757B5058EE20A" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Setaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="246" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="italica">
<emphasis id="76F577EC545251F6CFEF359291E3E9D7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="246">S. italica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
